commit.message:
build: exclude some paths from crate

The crate only has the capability to build a `stg` executable. As such,
much of the content of the repository is not useful in the crate
distribution. Excluding documentation, tests, and a few other ancilliary
directories shrinks the crate considerably.

commit.message:
fix: stdout from hooks

This repairs a regression that appeared in StGit 2.4.3 where the stdout from hooks would
not be output into the user's terminal.

This was due to gix_command::prepare() piping stdout by default.

Fixes: #418

commit.message:
ci: rollback to non-broken msys2-runtime

It appears that msys2-runtime 3.4.10-5 is the cause of `make prove`
breaking in the Windows build. This change forces an earlier
msys2-runtime package to be installed.
